    <h1 class="article-title">About WhereToWatchSportz</h1>
    <p class="article-description">Your guide to finding every match, on every platform, wherever you are.</p>

    <div class="article-rule"></div>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>WhereToWatchSportz helps sports fans quickly find out where to legally stream or watch live cricket, football, Formula 1, tennis and other major tournaments, no matter which country they're in.</p>

      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>Sports broadcasting rights change often and vary by country, which makes it genuinely confusing to know whether a tournament is on a free channel, a paid streaming app, or a satellite broadcaster. We track this information for major leagues and tournaments and present it clearly, broken down by country and platform.</p>

      <h2>How we keep information accurate</h2>
      <p>We review broadcaster and streaming rights ahead of major tournaments and update our pages whenever rights change hands between seasons. If you notice information that looks outdated or incorrect, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we'll review it promptly.</p>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <p>We do not host, stream, or distribute any sports broadcasts ourselves. We are purely an informational directory pointing you to official, licensed platforms where you can legally watch the sport you're looking for.</p>

      <h2>Our coverage</h2>
      <p>We currently cover cricket, football, Formula 1, and tennis, with more sports being added regularly as the site grows.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
